Date:11/14/2011 11:46:11 AM
From:E_K_S
Archer Daniels Midland Company (ADM)

ADM to Build Biodiesel Plant in Lloydminster, Canada
http://finance.yahoo.com/news/ADM-Build-Biodiesel-Plant-bw-2361943140.html?x=0&
=1

From the article:"...Archer Daniels Midland Company (NYSE: ADM - News) today
announced that it will build a 265 million liter (70 million gallon) biodiesel
plant in Lloydminster, Alberta, Canada, which will increase ADM’s North
American biodiesel production capacity by 50 percent. The biodiesel plant will
be located adjacent to the company’s existing canola crushing facility in
Lloydminster which will help optimize ADM’s agricultural origination,
transportation and processing assets in Canada.

“<u>The same agricultural processing operations we use to transform canola into
oil for food and meal for animal feed also provide ADM with the ability and
scale to efficiently produce cleaner-burning, renewable biodiesel</u>,” said
Mike Livergood, ADM vice president, global oleo chemicals. “This new biodiesel
facility will help support canola crush margins and capacity utilization at
this facility.” ...".

<snip>

"...In March, ADM announced plans to double the canola seed receiving
capabilities and storage capacity at the Lloydminster facility. The project,
which is expected to be completed by the end of the calendar year, includes the
construction of five new storage bins and a second receiving system, which is
expected to significantly reduce unloading times for area farmers....".

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----

ADM's biodiesel investment was spurred by Canada’s renewable diesel mandate
which now requires all diesel fuel and heating oil sold in Canada must contain
at least 2 percent biodiesel. By building the plant adjacent to their canola
oil processing facility, they can gain production efficiency both in crush
margins and higher plant utilization.

I missed buying more shares at the recent $24,00/share low available in early
October I have raised my GTC buy up to $25.00;share. At this time I only own a
small tracking position bought in 6/2011 at around the current price level . At
a forward PE of 9 and total LT debt only 4.3x annual earnings (at my upper end)
it fits my value mold. Typical of these AG plays, margins are small and ROA and
ROE are at the lower end (definitely not like IBM).

EKS
