Date:11/15/2011 2:26:40 PM
From:J Mako
Dennis,

re: FBN

Your NCAV doesn't look right.

NCAV = Current Asset - Total Liability.

It's a negative figure for FBN, not to mention it has another $181m off balance
sheet lease obligations. So, it's not a net-net.

Looks at its FCF in the last 3 years, probably you can argue it's cheap on
cashflow basis. But without backing of its asset value, it doesn't have the
margin of safety a true net-net offers.
%EOM----------------------

