NCAV = CA-CL
NET NET= CA-CL-LTD.
This is what I used.
I did not include off-balance sheet items. The theory is that if a business is
selling for 2/3 less than NCAV then it is worth more dead than alive so if a
business liquidated do they have to pay these lease obligations?
