Date:11/15/2011 4:49:27 PM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
Dennis3,

J Mako is right:

NCAV = CA - All Liabilities

There is very little reason to calculate CA-CL when other liabilities can be
arbitrarily huge. (There is some reason, but it's too technical to get into
here, since it's not what you think ;)). It's like people mistakenly claim that
some company has tons of cash without subtracting liabilities from that cash.

The theory is that if a business is selling for 2/3 less than NCAV then it is
worth more dead than alive...

Yes, but only if NCAV is calculated as J Mako (and me) calculate it. ;)
